<h1>CIS 371 Practice Midterm</h1>

<h2>JavaScript</h2>

<em>JavaScript is not on the midterm for Summer 2016.  Just PHP.</em>

<div id="js">
    <table>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <ul align="top">
                    <li>Write a JavaScript function <code>styleInvoice</code> that will add the total and subtotal to <a
                            href="robotInvoice.html"><code>robotInvoice.html</code></a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>Add CSS to format the invoice neatly.</li>
                    <li>Modify the width of the image to reflect the total. Make the width larger for smaller totals,
                        and smaller for larger totals.
                        (Don't worry about the details, just make sure you can use Javascript to modify the
                        <code>width</code> attribute of the <code>img</code> tag.)
                    </li>
                </ul>
                For more practice: Add an up arrow and a down arrow. Then put a handler on each arrow that will
                increase/descrease the size of the image.
            </td>
            <td>
                <img src="invoice_sample.png" width="400px">
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table>
</div>

